Think & Grow are working with a Brisbane based consumer technology company
that is experiencing rapid-growth and expanding globally. As the business
continues to grow, our client is looking for an exceptional CTO to lead,
develop, nurture and scale a medium sized engineering team that works
cohesively with the product team.

You will also focus on scaling the technology capability and launching
additional products that deliver beautiful customer experiences whilst
propelling the business through their next growth phase and beyond.

Reporting directly to the CEO and collaborating closely with the Founders, you
will assume a pivotal role in setting the technology and product strategy for
the company. Leading an established engineering and product team, you'll
oversee the development of new products and manage multiple projects
concurrently within tight deadlines. This position entails day-to-day
management to support strategic decision-making.

With direct accountability to the CEO, you will have oversight of engineering,
product, infrastructure, dev ops, quality assurance, and architecture.
Additionally, collaboration with key stakeholders in Marketing, Sales, and
Operational services is integral to the role.

Key Responsibilities:

  * Product Development Excellence - Own the product strategy, understand the product back to front and guide our key decisions on the products we build. Assess and embed the best product development processes for building our products, and platform. 
  * Data & Automation - Drive the use of high levels of automation. Leverage data to understand the health of the product, the performance of the team building the product, and customer sentiment, as well as openly communicating the information to the organisation. 
  * Internal Technologies - Utilise current technologies (PHP, React) and adopt a solution-oriented approach to identify capabilities that will improve and align with the overarching strategy. 
  * Budgets & Forecasting - Own the budget for the product and technology team. 
  * Security and Compliance - Our platform and systems are secure, with safeguards that prevent security breaches. 
  

Skills, Experience & Behaviours:

  * Technology Leader/Product -You should possess a minimum of 7 to 10 years of experience as a technology leader, with a background in product-led environments, preferably with exposure to B2B SaaS and Marketplaces. 
  * Engineering Development & Architecture - Experience Implementing modern development practices like pairing, continuous deployment, and test-driven development for scalability. Lead your team in building market-responsive software and architecture with an efficient development process and robust testing culture. 
  * Strategic Leadership - Define and spearhead commercial strategies for the product and technology functions, aligning them with company objectives. Contribute to shaping the company's strategy by providing insights into the product and technology landscape and its implications. Collaborate with leaders to align the product roadmap with the company's overall strategy, objectives, and key initiatives. Ensure a harmonious balance between commercial objectives and the technical and product vision, both in the short and long term, in alignment with the company's overarching strategy. 
  * People Leadership - Coach, inspire and engage developers to become a highly effective team. You will lead from the front, which means mentoring teams across product & technology, ensuring that they understand the vision of the organisation & how they can make an impact & contribute to the journey. You will also ensure teams are continuing their development to grow and build on their existing skills. 
  

An exciting opportunity awaits an experienced CTO with a passion for leading
high-performing technical and product teams. Your vision will be to foster a
culture of innovation and success. Leveraging a strong engineering background,
you'll elevate development systems and promote seamless collaboration between
technology and product teams. This role is also open to applications outside
of Brisbane, who are open to relocation.

